From 5a8c0f356e5a852c42c3e35b7a00986077c655d6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 16:23:57 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase D polish: sticky diff card headers

Each `KrtPrFlatDiff` card's header is now sticky against the outer
pane's scroll. While scrolling through a file's diff the header
stays at the top of the viewport so the user can always click it
to collapse. When the next card's content reaches the top, that
card's header takes over naturally (browsers stack sticky
siblings).

Two changes to make sticky work:

1. Replace `overflow: hidden` on `.krt-pr-flat-diff-card` with
   `clip-path: inset(0 round 6px)`. `overflow: hidden` traps a
   sticky child within the card's box (so it stops "sticking" to
   the outer scroll). `clip-path` clips the visual without
   affecting layout, so sticky still propagates to the outer
   `.krt-pr-editor` scroll context.
2. Set a solid background on the header so it covers the editor
   content as it slides under -- previously the header used a
   transparent fallback colour.

z-index: 5 keeps the header above Monaco's own overlay layers
inside the editor.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 .../krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css | 17 +++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css b/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css
index e3df418c5ee..d7059967206 100644
--- a/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css
+++ b/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css
@@ -816,7 +816,12 @@
 .krt-pr-flat-diff-card {
 	border: 1px solid var(--vscode-widget-border, rgba(127, 127, 127, 0.3));
 	border-radius: 6px;
-	overflow: hidden;
+	/* `clip-path` (not `overflow: hidden`) for the rounded-corner
+	 * clip so the sticky header below can escape the card and anchor
+	 * against the outer pane's scroll. `overflow: hidden` would
+	 * trap the sticky element inside the card and defeat its
+	 * stickiness. */
+	clip-path: inset(0 round 6px);
 	background: var(--vscode-editor-background);
 }
 
@@ -825,11 +830,19 @@
 	align-items: center;
 	gap: 10px;
 	padding: 6px 12px;
-	background: var(--vscode-editorGroupHeader-tabsBackground, transparent);
+	background: var(--vscode-editor-background);
 	border-bottom: 1px solid var(--vscode-widget-border, rgba(127, 127, 127, 0.25));
 	font-size: 12px;
 	cursor: pointer;
 	user-select: none;
+	/* Sticks to the top of the outer pane scroll while the user is
+	 * inside this file's diff. When the user scrolls past the card,
+	 * the next card's sticky header takes over naturally. z-index
+	 * above the editor's overlay so the header isn't covered by
+	 * Monaco's gutter / minimap. */
+	position: sticky;
+	top: 0;
+	z-index: 5;
 }
 
 .krt-pr-flat-diff-head:hover {
